social_posts.post_text: When your lawyer asks you to do his headshots but we end up channeling Tom Waits 🎼🚬 @aaronriedel

Coming out of Covid last year I made a promise to myself to explore all the places in the U.S. +++ that I had not been and fulfill dreams that I had put on hold. The past 16 months I have not been in one place more than 3 weeks at a time. Some might call it restlessness- but for me I’ve learned that keeping things moving, exploring and learning is what brings peace to my heart and inspiration for my work❤️ And my favorite part is all the beautiful people I meet along the way who are so full of love and kindly takes a solo traveler under their wing- cause if there is one thing I’ve learned, there are loving people everywhere who can’t wait to share what they have. ❤️❤️❤️
Where should I adventure next? 

(This past year I’ve been to Costa Rica, NYC, Memphis, Nashville, New Orleans, Jacumba Hot Springs, San Diego, Fresno, Los Angeles, Yosemite, San Francisco, Big Sur, Ojai, Santa Barbara, The O.C., Las Vegas, Lake Perris, Laguna Beach, Long Beach, Bombay Beach, Tecate & Valle De Guadalupe (Mexico), Oslo, Rome, Copenhagen edit+ Palm Springs, Yucca Valley, Joshua Tree)

Wandering the streets of Rome I was lucky to stumble upon these stylish fellas! Mid-sunset in front of the Colosseum I see 5 guys in suits jump on top of each other with a bunch of roses. And I’m like- this scenario is TOO good. After observing for a while they come up to me asking if I was a journalist and if I’d like to take some photos. Uhm YES PLEASE- and voila! Here’s our little impromptu film shoot!! They put a big smile on my face when I was actually feeling a bit blue. @blackbluesbrothers are an acrobatic performance group from Kenya who were in town to perform for the pope himself!! ✨

Dear friends, acquaintances or anyone in the industry- please keep an eye open for these unique vintage pieces. One of my dearest friends has had over $50k worth of furniture stolen from her warehouse not far from San Diego, CA. These are pieces collected over many years, that she has used to create beautiful spaces for people to come together. This absolutely breaks my heart 💔 She is one of the most hardworking, kind, caring and generous people I know. I pray that using this network and spreading the word can bring justice and she will have her life’s hard earned work back. Please share!! And if you see any pieces on Craig’s list, at events etc- please let me know. @humankinddesignstudio 
❤️🙏🏼✨

The year I fell in love with the Californian desert and it’s people, some wild horses and a couple of snakes. Exhibition coming in the spring!! Stay tuned for updates 🏜️🐍❤️

This is my beautiful friend Andres (the guy gesturing to the camera). He lives in the apartment above me in Brooklyn and always shares a smile and a beer with me outside on the stoop of our place. He’s lived in the building since 1981 and hardly knows a word English. So our communication mostly consists of “Hola- como estas”, smiles, fist bumps and cheers. I love how prevalent community is in NYC, if you ever feel alone you can just step out on the street and there will for sure be someone there happy to talk to you. My block mostly consist of people from Puerto Rico and the Dominican Republic, so every once in a while I get invited to dance some salsa in the bodega across the street or to one of the neighbors nieces birthday party. It’s incredible how much you can say without sharing the same language ❤️

Self-portrait 🐆

Have you ever seen your best self in a photo? A photo that captures the real you and that you are proud to present to the world? 

Most of us haven’t- and I believe it’s time to change that. I believe that every person on this planet is photogenic and to see that in your self can do so much for a persons self-esteem. Something that I’m really passionate about as I truly believe that every person has unique gifts they can contribute to the world and if we let ourselves shine- we light up the path for other people too 🤍✨ 

I’m offering Empowering Portraits sessions in NYC from Feb 17th- Feb 23th. Hit me up to secure your spot!

Portraits of strangers before and after sharing love stories 🤍🤍🤍

This is a project that has been brewing inside of me for years. Ever since I kissed a bunch of strangers I have been wondering how I could build on this project and communicate the same message that touches upon our common humanity. And then it hit me- LOVE. Sounds so simple and almost cliche, but it has been the driving force of my work ever since I started photographing. I have a love for people, I find everyone beautiful and it is so fascinating that we all are the protagonists of our own story. It doesn’t matter where we are from, how we look, what color our skin is, what we believe in, what political party we root for, at the end of the day we are all human beings wanting the same things for ourselves, friends and family: safety, joy and love. We are all one through love 🤍 Big thanks and shoutout to my friend @marvindeabreu for assisting and shooting BTS video ✨ #lovestories #portraitsofstrangers

We live in a society where everything is measured in likes, followers and statistics. I see so many young photographers starting out believing that they need to be amazing at their craft from day 1, or there’s no point in doing it. But if you don’t try, fail and try again- you’ll never discover new ways of shooting images, you might miss out on discovering a lighting technique you never thought about because it happened by accident, you’ll never become comfortable and secure in yourself knowing that you can solve any unexpected issue. So please let the perfectionism go, have fun, try, fail and do it all over again! 🫶🏼✨

Workshop coming soon for anyone who wants to learn more about how to shoot captivating portraits and become more secure in their path as a photographer 🤍

When I was 13 I made a mantra for myself: “If I have a positive thought about someone, I have to go tell them”. Because honestly why not? Little did I know that this idea would shape the rest of my life. I’ve probably met around 70% of the people I know in NYC on the street, and many of them have become close friends and even colleagues. It’s beautiful to watch how a compliment from a stranger can light someone’s face up and brighten their day. Honestly I think the purest joy I experience is to see other people light up. I believe we all want to feel seen, loved and accepted for who we are. As cheesy as it sounds, but a stranger is just a friend you haven’t met yet. Shoutout and big thanks to @thephotomack for filming BTS!!

When I was 13 I made a mantra for myself: “If I have a positive thought about someone, I have to go tell them”. Because honestly why not? Little did I know that this idea would shape how I live my everyday life. I’ve probably met around 70% of the people I know in NYC on the street, and many of them have become close friends and even colleagues. It’s beautiful to watch how a compliment from a stranger can light someone’s face up and brighten their day. Honestly I think the purest joy I experience is to see other people light up. I believe we all want to feel seen, loved and accepted for who we are. Everybody is somebody, a stranger is just a friend you haven’t met yet.

Brian struggles with a bad knee and makes due with the bare minimum. He was so kind and we ended up talking for a long time. He told me he usually never talks to people as he doesn’t want to bother them and that he really appreciated this encounter and will remember it forever 🥺❤️
